txt.en:
'Our overlord demands blood. I would stride forth and slaughter the Free Folk were Malavín not watching me like a craban.

'You, on the other hand, can make your way into the field and slaughter them for me. Succeed and I will see a portion of my strength transferred to you for a time.

'Slaughter them. Slaughter them all!'

<rgb=#FF0000>Accepting this quest will teleport you to the forward Orc camp in the Ettenmoors and expose your position on the Ettenmoors and mini-map.</rgb>
Be escorted by a scout into the Ettenmoors
Begin your glory seeking at the forward Orc Camp near Tol Ascarnen. Speak with Soldier Paashum to begin your conquest.

'Ah, to taste the flesh of man and drink the blood of Elves. I long for battle, [placeholder]. I will live through you vicariously for now. Mark my words, worm.

'I will rise and storm Glân Vraig and lay Lainedhal low before my time here is done.

'Go now! Make more chaos in your wake.'
<rgb=#FF0000>Failure: Get to near a rally point</rgb>
Stride through the front gate of Gramsfoot
Arrive at the forward Orc Camp near Tol Ascarnen
War-tyrant Akúlhun directs you to wade into the fray and slaughter the Free People. The more you kill the greater your reward will be. Be warned, all will know that you are on a rampage.
Scour the Ettenmoors for the enemies of Angmar and eliminate them where they are found. Slaughter for the glory of Angmar!
